summary: I had a dream. Bran had a vision of a wolf, lion and hound. He told Jaime this. The lion stayed behind while the wolf and hound...
body:
I had a dream. Bran had a vision of a wolf, lion and hound. He told Jaime this. The lion stayed behind while the wolf and hound climbed a mountain. They never came back. So Jaime decided this meant he had to join Arya and the Hound to kill the Mountain or they wouldn’t survive. Later it morphed to Jaime and Brienne teaching their daughter to wield a sword on a beach.

I can only hope D&D had a dream like this.

Hi! I’m still figuring out this tumblr thing – technology and I have always had a love/hate relationship – but I love to chat and geek out with people; feel free to drop me a line. 

What you’ll mainly see on this blog: fandom-related stuff (primarily fantasy, sci-fi, and procedural mystery), history, social justice/feminism, cute animals, puns, and random things that I think are interesting. 

Since learning (and unlearning) is a lifelong process, when I inevitably say something that is ignorant, offensive, and/or incorrect in any way, please feel free to call me out on it. I will always apologize and always do my best to not repeat my mistakes. 

Pronouns: she/her. 

You can also find me on FF.N and AO3 as Phosphorescent, on LJ as naidheachd, on WordPress as phosphorescentstars, & on Dreamwidth as phosphorescent_stars. (Be aware: I don't currently frequent the last 3 sites very often, but feel free to follow me on those accounts!)

summary: What are the "Bran’s revelations" you mentioned in your post? Visions? Characters coming back?
question: What are the "Bran’s revelations" you mentioned in your post? Visions? Characters coming back?
answer:
I have no idea. Leaker was not willing to reveal everything because “it endangered his job”. However he was adamant that Bran is not the king, neither did he confirm the proto-democracy ending. He made clear though that neither Dany nor Jon get the throne. He downright refused to reveal Tyrion’s fate after the trial and as for Jaime he just said he dies but also spoke of “Bran revelations”.

Leaker also said we might see Rhaegar flashbacks and a lot of God stuff. He said Bran communicates with three gods. On the other hand, he said we shouldn’t expect much from the prophecies but I am not entirely buying this, otherwise why would Davos and Tyrion discuss Melisandre’s death and Lord of Light’s sudden disappearance in S8E4?

My hope is that yes the plot twist he claims there is in the end is about Jaime. I mean, he’s a freaking main character. One of the big 5. If his point was to completely erase his character arc and return to his sister just to die without doing anything then why on earth does this character even exist in this story? Why does even Brienne exist? Nothing of their elaborate story would have a purpose or make sense.
